  {
    "text": "31",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "xlsx",
      "sheetName": "Sheet5"
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "Structural Elements",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "xlsx",
      "sheetName": "Sheet6"
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "Miscellaneous structural elements you can add to your document, like footnotes, endnotes, dropcaps and the like.",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "xlsx",
      "sheetName": "Sheet6"
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "Footnotes & Endnotes",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "xlsx",
      "sheetName": "Sheet6"
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "Footnotes1 and endnotesi are automatically recognized and both are converted to endnotes, with backlinks for maximum ease of use in ebook devices.",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "xlsx",
      "sheetName": "Sheet6"
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "Dropcaps",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "xlsx",
      "sheetName": "Sheet6"
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "D",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "xlsx",
      "sheetName": "Sheet6"
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "rop caps are used to emphasize the leading paragraph at the start of a section. In Word it is possible to specify how many lines of text a drop-cap should use.",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "xlsx",
      "sheetName": "Sheet6"
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "Links",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "xlsx",
      "sheetName": "Sheet6"
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "Two kinds of links are possible, those that refer to an external website and those that refer to locations inside the document itself. Both are supported by calibre. For example, here is a link pointing to the calibre download page. Then we have a link that points back to the section on paragraph level formatting in this document.",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "xlsx",
      "sheetName": "Sheet6"
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "Images",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "xlsx",
      "sheetName": "Sheet7"
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "Centered images like this are useful for large pictures that should be a focus of attention.",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "xlsx",
      "sheetName": "Sheet7"
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "There is no analogous technology in ebooks, so the conversion will usually end up placing the image either centered or floating close to the point in the text where it was inserted, not necessarily where it appears on the page in Word.",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "xlsx",
      "sheetName": "Sheet7"
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "Lists",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "xlsx",
      "sheetName": "Sheet8"
    }
  },
  {
    "text": "All types of lists are supported by the conversion, with the exception of lists that use fancy bullets, these get converted to regular bullets.",
    "metadata": {
      "sourceType": "xlsx",
      "sheetName": "Sheet8"
    }
  },
